rms. Tracing a strong lineage of pragmatism, romanticism, surrealism and dada in American intermedial works through the nineteenth century to the present day, the editors and authors of this volume chart a new and vital methodology for the study and appreciation of the correspondences between visual and verbal practices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArts, American - 21st century. 7aART / History / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican art.  aAmerican literature.  aAvant garde.  aEmbodied aesthetics.  aImage and text.  aInterdisciplinary.  aIntermedia.  aPragmatist aesthetics.1 aBlinder, Caroline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGander, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGander, Catherine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGarland, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarland, Sarah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMasuga, Katy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorgan-Owens, Jessie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPawlik, Joanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillips Brown, Julie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrice, Katie L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWarriner, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeingarden, Lauren S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610179240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526101792423Coveruhttps://www.degru